# Sales Forecasting Model

## 1. Data Loading and Preprocessing
```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# Load the dataset
data = pd.read_csv('Data_.csv')

# Preprocessing steps
# Handle missing values
data.fillna(method='ffill', inplace=True)

# Convert date column to datetime
# data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'])
```

## 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Total Sales by Month
monthly_sales = data.resample('M', on='date').sum()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x=monthly_sales.index, y='sales', data=monthly_sales)
plt.title('Total Sales by Month')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Total Sales')
plt.show()

# Transaction Trends
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.countplot(data=data, x='date')
plt.title('Transaction Trends')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

# More visualizations can be added as needed
```

## 3. Feature Engineering
```python
# Monthly Aggregation
monthly_data = data.resample('M').sum()

# Lag Features
monthly_data['sales_lag_1'] = monthly_data['sales'].shift(1)
```

## 4. Train-Test-Validation Split
```python
train = monthly_data['2023-01-01':'2023-07-31']
val = monthly_data['2023-08-01':'2023-09-30']
test = monthly_data['2023-10-01':'2023-12-31']
```

## 5. Random Forest Model Training and Evaluation
```python
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score

X_train = train[['sales_lag_1']]
y_train = train['sales']

rf_model = RandomForestRegressor()
rf_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predictions
rf_predictions = rf_model.predict(test[['sales_lag_1']])
rmse_rf = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test['sales'], rf_predictions))
r2_rf = r2_score(test['sales'], rf_predictions)
```

## 6. XGBoost Model Training and Evaluation
```python
import xgboost as xgb

xgb_model = xgb.XGBRegressor()
xgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predictions
xgb_predictions = xgb_model.predict(test[['sales_lag_1']])
rmse_xgb = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test['sales'], xgb_predictions))
r2_xgb = r2_score(test['sales'], xgb_predictions)
```

## 7. Comparison Visualizations
```python
# R² Score
models = ['Random Forest', 'XGBoost']
results = [r2_rf, r2_xgb]
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
sns.barplot(x=models, y=results)
plt.title('Model Comparison: R² Score')
plt.show()

# RMSE Visualization
rmse_results = [rmse_rf, rmse_xgb]
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
sns.barplot(x=models, y=rmse_results)
plt.title('Model Comparison: RMSE')
plt.show()
```

## 8. Prediction Results Table
```python
results_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Actual': test['sales'],
    'Predicted_RF': rf_predictions,
    'Predicted_XGB': xgb_predictions
})
print(results_df)
```

## 9. Error Analysis
```python
results_df['Error_RF'] = (results_df['Actual'] - results_df['Predicted_RF']) / results_df['Actual'] * 100
results_df['Error_XGB'] = (results_df['Actual'] - results_df['Predicted_XGB']) / results_df['Actual'] * 100
```

